metaData.descriptionCS: The child mentally solves a series of orally presented arithmetic problems within a specified time limit.

questions.title: †Item 1. Birds
questions.correctInstructionsHTML:
Correct response [Correctly counts from 1 to 3]:

Say, Let’s try another one.
questions.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

†Say, That’s not quite right. Watch me and listen carefully.

Point to each of the three birds (about one per second) from the child’s left to right while counting aloud and then say, There are three birds. Let’s try another one.

questions.title: †Item 2. Chicks
questions.correctInstructionsHTML:
Correct response [Correctly counts from 1 to 5]:

Say, Let's try another one.
questions.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

†Say, That's not quite right. Watch me and listen carefully.

Point to each of the five chicks (about one per second) from the child's left to right while counting aloud and then say, There are five chicks. Let's try another one.

questions.title: †Item 3. Trees
questions.correctInstructionsHTML:
Correct response [Correctly counts from 1 to 10]:

Say, Let’s try another one.
questions.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

†Point and say, That’s not quite right. Watch me and listen carefully.

Point to each of the 10 trees (about one per second) from the child’s left to right while counting aloud and then say, There are ten trees. Let’s try another one.

consecutiveZerosDiscontinueRule.description: This subtest discontinues after 4 consecutive scores of 0 points.
